The package you are installing is part of Rudix.

Rudix is a collection of Unix software delivered as packages for Mac OS X. Every package is self-contained and has everything it needs to work.

Rudix tries its best not to add extra dependencies to anything but the native Mac OS X libraries.

Binaries, libraries, documentation and other files will be installed in /usr/local/ folder. Python modules will be installed in the /Library/Python/2.6/site-packages/ folder.

You will now be guided through the steps necessary to install this software.

Thank you for choosing Rudix!